text: Saal an der Saale is a municipality in Rhön-Grabfeld in Bavaria in Germany. It is on the river Fränkische Saale. The municipality has the two townships Saal an der Saale and Waltershausen. Ever since the 1978 municipal reform, it has been the seat of the joint administration of these independent communities: Wülfershausen, Großeibstadt, and Saal an der Saale. The entire administrative area is home to about 4200 residents as of 2008. ==References== Category:Rhön-Grabfeld
